<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  
  {%- comment -%}
    The <title> tag sets the page title in the browser tab.
    {{ shop.name }} is a Liquid variable that automatically pulls
    your store’s name from Shopify settings.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <title>{{ shop.name }}</title>

  {%- comment -%}
    This links your CSS file stored in /assets/style.css.
    'asset_url' is a filter that converts the file name into
    the full Shopify CDN URL for that asset.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'style.css' | asset_url }}">

  {%- comment -%}
    {{ content_for_header }} is REQUIRED by Shopify.
    It automatically injects critical scripts, metadata, apps, etc.
    Without this line, some apps and Shopify features won’t load properly.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {{ content_for_header }}
</head>

<body>
  {%- comment -%}
    {% section 'header' %} will include your header.liquid section.
    Typically contains navigation, logo, cart link, etc.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {% section 'header' %}

  {%- comment -%}
    {{ content_for_layout }} is a placeholder where Shopify
    injects the main page template (like index.liquid or collection.liquid).
    For example: when viewing home page → index.liquid content is shown here.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {{ content_for_layout }}

  {%- comment -%}
    {% include 'footer' %} pulls in your footer.liquid file
    from the snippets/ folder. It shows the footer section at the bottom.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {% render 'footer' %}
</body>
</html>
